The top officials of the government never issued a warning.
Can we really claim that investors must bear all the consequences of their losses?
How could this be fair?
The world is discovering the power of capitalism and how it transforms economies.
Yet capitalism relies on trust and faith.
An unfairly treated result can be fatal for economic growth, as it means people lose trust in companies and are less willing to provide them with their valuable capital and labor.
Is such a result morally preferable to a bailout?
